evidence: The hot-worked TiNbTa 0.5 ZrAl 0.5 alloy has a high compressive yield strength of 1740 MPa with a considerable compressive ductility of 12% at room temperature.

The mechanical properties of the as-forged TiNbTa 0.5 ZrAl 0.5 alloy are as follows: σ 0.2 = 1740 MPa, σ m = 2031 MPa, and δ = 12% at room temperature. In view of the low density (7.3 g/ cm 3 determined by Archimedes method), the hot-worked TiNb-Ta 0.5 ZrAl 0.5 alloy has a high specific strength.
The hot-worked TiNbTa 0.5 ZrAl 0.5 RHEA has a high compressive yield strength of 1740 MPa with a considerable compressive plasticity of 12% at room temperature.
